<section xml:id="sec-8-1-Sequences_and_Recursion" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Sequences and Recursion</title>
    <p><em>Sequences and Recursion</em> introduces the notation and terminology associated with sequences of numbers. 
        The connection between <em>sequences</em> and <em>functions</em> is discussed. The details 
        <xref ref="sec-8-2-Sigma_Notation" text="title"/>, <xref ref="sec-8-3-Arithmetic_Sequences_and_Series" text="title"/>
         and <xref ref="sec-8-4-Geometric_Sequences_and_Series" text="title"/> are saved for other lessons, 
         though they are foreshadowed in this topic.</p>
        
